        "heading": "The approach",
        "body": "Relay serializes a live session into a continuation contract: a signed, portable document that captures intent, plans, and in-flight code. A daemon drives the workflow through a finite state machine, manages an adapter per provider, watches quota burn across every connected account, and forecasts when an agent will run out. Before the wall arrives it routes the contract to a fresh agent or provider, so work resumes instead of restarting. Decisions and constraints persist in a knowledge graph so context survives the switch.",
